CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 31, 1959, pg. B2 reads: " "King And Queen" Crowned - The "Queen" is charming Jayne Wright of Norristown, and the lucky "King" is Joseph Warden of Pittsburgh. Their crowning climaxed a dance Saturday night, following a banquet in Hotel Sherwyn.  Left to right are attendants: Alfred Pollit, Mainline; Seretha Jones, Mercer County; Fanny Yellock, Beaver Valley; Patricia Peyton, Dauphin County; Josephine taylor, Erie; Terry Woodyard, York; and John Coleman. - Harris photos."
TitMainTitle: "Queen" Jayne Wright and "King" Joseph Warden, seated in front of court, from left: Alfred Pollit, Seretha Jones, Fanny Yellock, Patricia Peyton, Josephine Taylor, Terry Woodyard, and John Coleman, posed in Hotel Sherwyn for NAACP banquet and dance
